articles.title: Super blood Moon: everything you need to know about the lunar eclipse - The Conversation UK
articles.description: A total lunar eclipse will be visible from parts of Australia, Asia and the western parts of North and South America on May 26.
articles.content: Throughout history, lunar eclipses have seemed dramatic. The Moons grey-white disc deepens to yellow and orange and finally a dark red cast this gives a lunar eclipse its nickname of the blood Moon. … [+3469 chars]
